                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_æjjafyn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>æjjafyn</orth><form type="participle"><orth>æjjæft</orth></form></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>æjjafun</orth><form type="participle"><orth>æjjaft</orth></form></form><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>догонять</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>overtake</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>настигать</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>reach</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>застигать</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>catch</q></abv:tr></sense></sense><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>переносить</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>undergo</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>испытывать</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>go through</q></abv:tr></sense></sense><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>rnæ sær cy næ bajjæfta!</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>чего только моя голова не испытала!</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>what has my head not went through!</q></abv:tr></abv:example><abv:example><quote>ærbajjæfta qazty wæd iw dardbæstag</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>нагнал тогда гусей один чужеземец</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>then a stranger caught up with the geese</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>88</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>fændagyl sæ bajjæfta</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>по дороге он нагнал их (братьев)</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>on his way he overtook them (brothers)</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>44</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>bajjæfta sæ æmbīsfændagyl</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>нагнал их на полдороге</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>caught up with them halfway</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>66</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>æjjafun æj bajdadta</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>стала его настигать</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>(she) began to overtake him</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>18%l10%l</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>ærbabæj æj æjjafta</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>догнала опять его</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>(she) caught up with him again</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>18%l8%l</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>Sozyryqojy sūryn bajdydta; Færdyǵy bydyry jæ nyjjæfta</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>стал он преследовать Созрыко; нагнал его на Фардыгской равнине</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>he began to pursue Sozryko; caught up with him on the Fardyg plain</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 40</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>rnæ læppū dæ fyccaǵydær æjjafʒænī æmæ myn yn mасу kæn</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>мой сын первый тебя настигнет, но ты ничего ему не делай (плохого)</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>my son will overtake you first, but you don't do anything (bad) to him</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>83</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>xæræg bæxi ne ʽjjāfuj</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>осел коня не догонит</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>the donkey will not catch up with the horse</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>74</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>kæd mа jæ ūdægasæj sæjjafin</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>авось я еще застану его в живых</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>maybe I'll find him alive again</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 64</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>binontæj xæʒary nikæj bajjæfton</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>из домочадцев никого не застал дома</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>he did not find anyone from the household at home</q></abv:tr></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>avd wæjugemæ baqærdtæj, xusgæ sæ bajjafta</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>он добрался до семи великанов, застал их спящими</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>he got to the seven giants, found them sleeping</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>28%l11%l</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>qæbær æfxwærd ba æjjafta xwænxon silgojmag</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сильное притеснение терпела горская женщина</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>the highland woman endured severe oppression</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_FS"/><biblScope>I 55</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>fons ǧudgond ne ʽjjafuncæ</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>скот не находит (надлежащего) ухода</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>the cattle does not find (proper) care</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>280%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Как и <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>yāftan: yāb-</w> <gloss><q>находить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/> <gloss><q>достигать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/> <gloss><q>испытывать</q></gloss></mentioned>, восходит к древнеарийскому %iāр-%i ‘достигать’ [[Перс. %iyāftan%i из %i*adi-āp-%i или %i*abi-āp-%i? <bibl><author>Szemerényi</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_JAOS"/><biblScope>1950 1.ХХ 229</biblScope></bibl>.]] Кроме <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>yāftan</w></mentioned>, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="hac"><lang/> <w>yāw-</w> <gloss><q>достигать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hac"><w/> <gloss><q>настигать</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>KPF, Abt.</author><biblScope>III</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl><author>Bd.</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">II, стр. 200</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">II, p. 200</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/> <w>f(ẹr)-āp</w> <gloss><q>достигать</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Зарубин._Барт."/><biblScope>48</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/> <w>biyāp-: biyaptā</w> <gloss><q>догонять</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Андреев._Ягн."/></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>patiyāp(ptyyʼp)</w> <gloss><q>достигать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/> <w>pərow</w> <gloss><q>находить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/> <w>pry’b-: pryft</w> <gloss><q>достигать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><w/> <gloss><q>находить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>āyāftan, yāftan</w> <gloss><q>достигать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/> <w>āyāpak</w> <gloss><q>достигший счастья</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><w/> <gloss><q>осчастливленный</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Nyberg"/><biblScope>II 28</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>byau-, byēh</w></mentioned> (← %i*vi-āp-%i: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Leumann"/><biblScope>III 479</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Konow._SSt."/><biblScope>128</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>ā̌р-, apayeiti</w> <gloss><q>достигать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>настигать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>нагонять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>āp-, apnōti</w> <gloss><q>достигать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>нагонять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>доходить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>apiscor</w> <gloss><q>достигать</q></gloss></mentioned>. %bСкифское%b собственное имя <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/> <w>Ιάφαγος</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Латышев"/><biblScope>I 131</biblScope></bibl>) отвечает осетинскому %iæjjafæg%i и означало, надо думать, „настигающий“ (<bibl><author>Вс. Миллер</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ЖМНП"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1886, окт., стр. 247</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1886, oct., p. 247</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Vasmer._Ir._i._S."/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>). Начальное %iæ%i — остаток преверба <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æv-"/> (%i*abi-āp-%i) или <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æm-"/> (%i*ham-vi-āp-%i), согласный элемент которого ассимилировался (ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æværyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwajyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwændyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwærdyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwīlyn"/>, а также д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æjjevun"/>). Во всяком случае бесспорно, что глагол существовал на осетинской почве и без начального %iæ-%i, в форме %i*jafyn%i (ср. выше <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/> <w>Ιάφαγος</w></mentioned> и даже %iafun%i (%iwinun æj bajdajuj%i, %iafun æj bajdajuj%i „он начинает его видеть, начинает его нагонять“, — сказание о Нарте Сослане в записи М. Туганова, рукопись); ср. сосуществование <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wændyn"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwændyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wærdyn"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwærdyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wīlyn"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwīlyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_īvyn"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æjjevun"/>. Простейший корень %iāp-%i сохранился в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afun"/> и, может быть, в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afon"/> ‘пора’, ‘срок’ и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afæʒ"/> ‘год’, q. v.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 49</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>42</biblScope></bibl>, — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>190, 213</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Like <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>yāftan: yāb-</w> <gloss><q>find</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/> <gloss><q>reach</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/> <gloss><q>undergo</q></gloss></mentioned>, goes back to the ancient Aryan %iāр-%i ‘reach’ [[Persian %iyāftan%i is from %i*adi-āp-%i or %i*abi-āp-%i? <bibl><author>Szemerényi</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_JAOS"/><biblScope>1950 1.ХХ 229</biblScope></bibl>.]] Besides <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>yāftan</w></mentioned>, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="hac"><lang/> <w>yāw-</w> <gloss><q>reach</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hac"><w/> <gloss><q>overtake</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>KPF, Abt.</author><biblScope>III</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl><author>Bd.</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">II, стр. 200</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">II, p. 200</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/> <w>f(ẹr)-āp</w> <gloss><q>reach</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Зарубин._Барт."/><biblScope>48</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/> <w>biyāp-: biyaptā</w> <gloss><q>catch up</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Андреев._Ягн."/></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>patiyāp(ptyyʼp)</w> <gloss><q>reach</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/> <w>pərow</w> <gloss><q>find</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/> <w>pry’b-: pryft</w> <gloss><q>reach</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><w/> <gloss><q>find</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>āyāftan, yāftan</w> <gloss><q>reach</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/> <w>āyāpak</w> <gloss><q>having found happiness</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><w/> <gloss><q>blessed</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Nyberg"/><biblScope>II 28</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>byau-, byēh</w></mentioned> (← %i*vi-āp-%i: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Leumann"/><biblScope>III 479</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Konow._SSt."/><biblScope>128</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>ā̌р-, apayeiti</w> <gloss><q>reach</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>overtake</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>catch up</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>āp-, apnōti</w> <gloss><q>reach</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>catch up</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>come up</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>apiscor</w> <gloss><q>reach</q></gloss></mentioned>. The %bScythian%b proper name<mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/> <w>Ιάφαγος</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Латышев"/><biblScope>I 131</biblScope></bibl>) corresponds to the Ossetic %iæjjafæg%i and meant, supposedly, “overtaking” (<bibl><author>Вс. Миллер</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ЖМНП"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1886, окт., стр. 247</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1886, oct., p. 247</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Vasmer._Ir._i._S."/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>). The initial %iæ%i is the remnant preverb <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æv-"/> (%i*abi-āp-%i) or <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æm-"/> (%i*ham-vi-āp-%i), where the consonant element assimilated (cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æværyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwajyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwændyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwærdyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwīlyn"/>, and Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æjjevun"/>). In any case, it is indisputable that the verb is of Ossetic origin and occurred without initial %iæ-%i, in the shape of %i*jafyn%i (see above <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/> <w>Ιάφαγος</w></mentioned> and even %iafun%i (%iwinun æj bajdajuj%i, %iafun æj bajdajuj%i “he begins to see him, begins to catch up with him,” — the legend about Nart Soslan in M. Tuganovʼs notes, manuscript); compare with co-existing <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wændyn"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwændyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wærdyn"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwærdyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wīlyn"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æwwīlyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_īvyn"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æjjevun"/>. The simple stem %iāp-%i was preserved in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afun"/> and, probably, in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afon"/> ‘season’, ‘term’ and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_afæʒ"/> ‘year’, q. v.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 49</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>42</biblScope></bibl>, — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>190, 213</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>